C++ Mastery Design Doc

Flow start from - Main.cpp file.

For logging purpose use-
debug.print
debug.debug
info.info
error.error

To get rid of opening and closing formatting in code you can set project 
environment to dev.
E.g.
/* 
===============================
   Welcome to C++ OOP Mastery
===============================

Please hold on...

Getting things ready for your OOP adventure... 

===============================
   All systems are go! <3
===============================
Program execution started.*/

Go to Environment.cpp file and change 
static Environment currentEnv = Environment::Prod;  
to
static Environment currentEnv = Environment::Dev;  
This will directly run the main code.

To include header file prefer global.h as it include all imp file and local header file.


